Artemis was a Virgin Huntress; the Greeks called her the Huntress  of Souls.  She protected the wild places and animals; to her was known the deep places in Nature where one could rest and regain strength.  Violence for itself was abhorrent to her, yet she was swift to deal out punishment to offenders, especially those who threatened or harrassed women. <br>
